1
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:19,541
[MAID 9A]
Anna, Ellina, and Leasya.

2
00:00:19,625 --> 00:00:22,125
Deploy to the specified area.

3
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:24,458
[STRAFANSKY]
Initiating Phase 2.

4
00:00:24,541 --> 00:00:28,250
Our top priority
is securing the target!

5
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,250
Your Highness!

6
00:00:29,333 --> 00:00:31,250
Yes, what is it?

7
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:32,916
There's an urgent letter.

8
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:34,166
Where is it from?

9
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:36,041
It says Japan, Your Highness.

10
00:00:36,125 --> 00:00:37,708
Is that so?

11
00:00:41,291 --> 00:00:42,541
[MAID 9A]
Target's been spotted.

12
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:44,375
Commencing operation.

13
00:00:45,416 --> 00:00:47,833
[FEMALE BUTLER 9A]
What's wrong, Your Highness?

14
00:00:47,916 --> 00:00:49,791
I've been called away.

15
00:00:49,875 --> 00:00:52,041
I leave this mission
in your hands.

16
00:00:52,125 --> 00:00:54,583
What could be so urgent
that you have to go now?

17
00:00:55,083 --> 00:00:57,541
[STRAFANSKY] My presence
is required elsewhere.

18
00:00:57,625 --> 00:00:59,583
A school festival.

19
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:05,458
A school festival?

20
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:41,500
[STUDENT chattering]

21
00:02:49,458 --> 00:02:50,958
[YAYOI]
Okay, ladies!

22
00:02:51,041 --> 00:02:53,125
We all have a lot of work to do
in a very short amount of time,

23
00:02:53,208 --> 00:02:55,333
but please don't
cut any corners.

24
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,875
[YAYOI]
Karin!

25
00:02:58,958 --> 00:03:00,708
--[YAYOI yelling]
--[KARIN crying]

26
00:03:00,791 --> 00:03:03,166
[NINA]
Are you--really a witch?

27
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:04,625
[LION]
The people of this strange world

28
00:03:04,708 --> 00:03:07,500
say that name
whenever they see me.

29
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:09,958
[MAHIRO]
Cut!

30
00:03:10,041 --> 00:03:12,125
Lion, you are way off again.

31
00:03:12,208 --> 00:03:13,666
[BELLE whines]

32
00:03:14,625 --> 00:03:16,333
You need to get into character.

33
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:18,958
Try acting like a Foreigner
who's lost on Septpia.

34
00:03:19,041 --> 00:03:20,625
[BELLE squeaks]

35
00:03:22,125 --> 00:03:23,208
[LION]
Okay.

36
00:03:23,291 --> 00:03:25,708
[MAHIRO]
Let's take five everybody.

37
00:03:31,666 --> 00:03:33,833
I'm a Foreigner
who's gotten lost.

38
00:03:33,916 --> 00:03:34,875
--[footsteps]
--I'm a Foreigner

39
00:03:34,958 --> 00:03:37,083
--[footsteps]
--who's gotten lost.

40
00:03:37,166 --> 00:03:39,375
So this is where
you've been hiding.

41
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,083
[LION]
Oh, hey.

42
00:03:42,166 --> 00:03:44,625
[NINA] Mahiro asked me
to come find you.

43
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:49,500
[LION] I guess it's time
to rehearse again.

44
00:03:49,583 --> 00:03:50,375
Sorry.

45
00:03:50,458 --> 00:03:52,375
Why are you apologizing?

46
00:03:52,458 --> 00:03:55,500
Because I'm dragging
everyone else in the play down.

47
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:58,291
You're just nervous because
people are looking at you.

48
00:03:58,375 --> 00:03:59,958
Let's talk to Mahiro.

49
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:02,541
We'll tell her
we wanna practice alone.

50
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:04,458
Really?

51
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:05,958
Thanks a lot!

52
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:09,541
[LION giggles]

53
00:04:11,583 --> 00:04:14,083
What an interesting young lady
you turned out to be.

54
00:04:14,166 --> 00:04:16,458
Now drink some of this
morning dew!

55
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:19,333
It will help quench your thirst!

56
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:21,333
Just stop for a second.

57
00:04:21,416 --> 00:04:22,916
What'd I do wrong now?

58
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,833
[NINA] It's the same problem--
your speech sounds unnatural.

59
00:04:25,916 --> 00:04:27,958
Uh, well, I thought
the best way

60
00:04:28,041 --> 00:04:29,958
to show that she was
from a different world

61
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:31,500
is to have my
Foreigner character

62
00:04:31,583 --> 00:04:34,708
talk a little bit weirder
than the people of Septpia.

63
00:04:34,791 --> 00:04:37,416
I get that, but you're
way overthinking it.

64
00:04:37,500 --> 00:04:39,333
[LION]
Are you sure?

65
00:04:39,416 --> 00:04:40,708
[NINA]
Listen.

66
00:04:40,791 --> 00:04:43,250
The way you're reading
the role now isn't working.

67
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:47,125
Try acting as if the girl in the
play is actually you instead.

68
00:04:47,208 --> 00:04:50,500
[STUDENTS chattering]

69
00:04:50,583 --> 00:04:52,833
[KARIN] Mistress,
the props are halfway done,

70
00:04:52,916 --> 00:04:54,250
but we're
running low on supplies

71
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:57,250
and need to go shopping
if we hope to finish on time.

72
00:04:57,333 --> 00:04:59,125
Sorry, but the costumes
are taking us

73
00:04:59,208 --> 00:05:00,583
longer than we expected.

74
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:03,083
The set builders are
having a lot of trouble.

75
00:05:03,166 --> 00:05:05,625
Where do you want
lighting and sound set up?

76
00:05:05,708 --> 00:05:08,625
[YAYOI] Things aren't moving
as smoothly as I'd planned.

77
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:11,125
The path to great theater's
a harsh one.

78
00:05:11,208 --> 00:05:12,500
[BELLE squeaks]

79
00:05:12,583 --> 00:05:13,708
[sighs]

80
00:05:13,791 --> 00:05:15,500
I'll leave the actors'
performances to you,

81
00:05:15,583 --> 00:05:16,750
Director Mahiro.

82
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:18,250
Roger that.

83
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:21,291
And I trust you to handle
all the behind-the-scenes work.

84
00:05:21,375 --> 00:05:24,041
I intend to
meet those expectations.

85
00:05:24,125 --> 00:05:27,041
But I really wish we all had
a little more time on our hands.

86
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:29,833
No kidding, the acting's
still got a long way to go.

87
00:05:29,916 --> 00:05:31,083
Things are gonna
get pretty rough

88
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:33,083
if we can't figure stuff out.

89
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,916
I just thought of
the perfect idea.

90
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:36,958
[BELLE squeaks]

91
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:39,875
I propose extended prep hours!

92
00:05:39,958 --> 00:05:42,125
There's no way we'll
make it at this rate!

93
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:43,958
--[RINO sighs]
--[KAGURA] Oh yeah?

94
00:05:44,041 --> 00:05:45,291
[school bell chimes]

95
00:05:45,375 --> 00:05:47,291
[KOZUE] This is a
special announcement.

96
00:05:47,375 --> 00:05:48,708
Starting tomorrow after school

97
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:50,500
and ending
the following morning,

98
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:52,833
we will be open for students
to stay overnight

99
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:54,958
and prepare for the festival.

100
00:05:55,041 --> 00:05:56,000
[STUDENTS]
Yay!

101
00:05:56,083 --> 00:05:57,625
[KOZUE]
Please use your time wisely,

102
00:05:57,708 --> 00:05:59,791
so that we may open
the first school festival

103
00:05:59,875 --> 00:06:02,125
in tip-top form.

104
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:04,000
It's so on tomorrow!

105
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:05,583
Yay! Whoo!

106
00:06:05,666 --> 00:06:06,916
That's a relief, huh?

107
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:09,000
Now we can practice
all night long.

108
00:06:09,083 --> 00:06:10,375
Huh?

109
00:06:10,458 --> 00:06:11,916
Huh...?

110
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
[STUDENTS chattering]

111
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:17,541
Just move it over
a little more to the right!

112
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:19,750
Wow! Look at that banner.

113
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:21,541
[BELLE squeaks]

114
00:06:22,708 --> 00:06:24,291
Miss Pirari?

115
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:29,125
[LION]
Do you think it's possible

116
00:06:29,208 --> 00:06:31,750
that the two of us
could ever be friends?

117
00:06:31,833 --> 00:06:35,208
Because I'd like
to have a friend.

118
00:06:35,291 --> 00:06:37,625
That's not right.

119
00:06:37,708 --> 00:06:40,000
I know how this girl feels.

120
00:06:40,083 --> 00:06:41,916
[LION hums]

121
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:44,041
[LION giggles]

122
00:06:44,125 --> 00:06:46,000
[LION]
You're it, Mr. Bear!

123
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:51,083
[LION laughs]

124
00:07:07,166 --> 00:07:10,833
Do you think it's possible that
the two of us could be friends?

125
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,791
[NINA]
Of course.

126
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,416
But is there a reason
you're asking?

127
00:07:17,708 --> 00:07:18,833
It's just--

128
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:22,583
I haven't had a friend
in a very long time.

129
00:07:25,208 --> 00:07:27,666
[NINA]
You said those lines perfectly.

130
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:29,041
[LION]
Really?

131
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:31,333
[NINA]
Just keep saying them like that.

132
00:07:31,416 --> 00:07:36,375
[STUDENTS chattering]

133
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:40,500
Let's get through this
without any hiccups, ladies!

134
00:07:40,583 --> 00:07:42,375
[STUDENTS cheer]

135
00:07:42,458 --> 00:07:44,000
[KARIN yells]

136
00:07:44,083 --> 00:07:46,208
[KAREN yells]

137
00:07:50,666 --> 00:07:52,708
Everybody's been
working so hard.

138
00:07:52,791 --> 00:07:55,083
And the Miss Pirari
contest's a hit.

139
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:56,708
I wonder who's gonna win.

140
00:07:56,791 --> 00:07:59,083
Yeah, it's a total mystery.

141
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,875
[MAHIRO] Now all that's
left to fix is the acting.

142
00:08:13,708 --> 00:08:15,500
Time to show 'em I got better!

143
00:08:15,583 --> 00:08:17,125
You sure practiced a lot.

144
00:08:17,208 --> 00:08:18,291
Yup!

145
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:20,833
Huh?! I'm excited
to see what you've got!

146
00:08:25,750 --> 00:08:28,083
Do you think it's possible
that the two of us

147
00:08:28,166 --> 00:08:29,541
could ever be friends?

148
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:32,000
[MAHIRO groans]

149
00:08:32,083 --> 00:08:36,333
No matter how much I beg, the
god of acting won't visit Lion.

150
00:08:36,416 --> 00:08:39,375
[NINA] But you said
the lines right yesterday.

151
00:08:39,458 --> 00:08:42,708
We only have the auditorium for
a limited amount of time today.

152
00:08:42,791 --> 00:08:45,291
So, how about you Trance
and try the scene again?

153
00:08:45,375 --> 00:08:46,666
[LION]
Sure...

154
00:08:48,791 --> 00:08:51,166
I trust you're
a girl of your word,

155
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:53,791
and you haven't forgotten
your promise to me.

156
00:08:55,541 --> 00:08:56,750
I haven't.

157
00:08:56,833 --> 00:08:58,041
Then you know.

158
00:08:58,125 --> 00:09:00,875
It's meaningless
to rely on me and my power.

159
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:03,708
This is the performance
I've been dreaming about!

160
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:06,708
Really? That's how
you want me to act?

161
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:08,541
Yes, it was perfect!

162
00:09:10,541 --> 00:09:11,833
[LION]
Yay!

163
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:14,333
Let's rehearse it again
really fast before I forget!

164
00:09:14,416 --> 00:09:16,416
I trust you're
a girl of your word

165
00:09:16,500 --> 00:09:19,916
and that you haven't forgotten
the promise you made to me.

166
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,291
[STUDENTS whine]

167
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:24,041
--She's bad again--
--Well, we don't have a choice.

168
00:09:24,125 --> 00:09:26,208
Lion's gonna have to do
the entire performance

169
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:28,000
while Tranced with Rosa.

170
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:32,291
[MIZUKI]
Attention all Pirari students!

171
00:09:32,375 --> 00:09:35,375
Today's the day you've all
been working so hard for!

172
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:37,791
It's the very first
Pirari Festival

173
00:09:37,875 --> 00:09:39,666
our school has ever hosted.

174
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:41,708
So, it's not an
exaggeration to say that

175
00:09:41,791 --> 00:09:43,416
the success of today's events

176
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:45,583
rides on each and
every student here.

177
00:09:45,666 --> 00:09:48,708
Therefore, I ask that we all
take a moment to consider

178
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:51,000
the significance of
Septpia's coexistence

179
00:09:51,083 --> 00:09:52,333
with alternate worlds,

180
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:55,291
with respect to Pirari's
foundation and history.

181
00:09:55,375 --> 00:09:58,458
And to make sure we put on the
best school festival possible.

182
00:09:58,541 --> 00:10:01,750
I invite everyone to have
as much fun as they can!

183
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:04,875
The first Pirari School
festival is now open!

184
00:10:04,958 --> 00:10:07,208
[STUDENTS cheer]

185
00:10:07,291 --> 00:10:09,375
Looks like things have started.

186
00:10:09,458 --> 00:10:11,791
Our class performance
isn't until this afternoon,

187
00:10:11,875 --> 00:10:14,041
so you're free to enjoy
the festival until then.

188
00:10:14,125 --> 00:10:14,958
[STUDENTS cheer]

189
00:10:15,041 --> 00:10:17,833
[CROWD chattering]

190
00:10:17,916 --> 00:10:20,250
[BOOTH VENDOR 9A] Two grilled
Monoliums, coming right up!

191
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:26,333
So delicious!

192
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,333
But I wonder what
kind of meat this is.

193
00:10:28,416 --> 00:10:29,333
Who cares?

194
00:10:29,416 --> 00:10:31,458
We'll take two more.

195
00:10:31,541 --> 00:10:33,541
Over here are the
villager costumes.

196
00:10:33,625 --> 00:10:34,708
They're perfect.

197
00:10:34,791 --> 00:10:36,333
And all the props are prepared.

198
00:10:36,416 --> 00:10:37,833
The villagers all look good.

199
00:10:37,916 --> 00:10:39,791
I can put those down
as completed.

200
00:10:39,875 --> 00:10:42,083
How about the other costumes?

201
00:10:42,166 --> 00:10:44,583
I can't believe there's
so much good food here!

202
00:10:44,666 --> 00:10:46,875
I hope we can find
a nice spot to sit.

203
00:10:46,958 --> 00:10:48,458
[BELLE squeaks]

204
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:50,958
--[LION gasps]
--Oh.

205
00:10:51,041 --> 00:10:52,833
Welcome, ladies!

206
00:10:52,916 --> 00:10:54,166
[LION]
Good morning, Yuko!

207
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,166
Is there a reason
you've Tranced?

208
00:10:56,250 --> 00:10:59,333
[YUKO] Yes, our class is
hosting a Tetra-Heaven cafe.

209
00:10:59,416 --> 00:11:01,666
Would you two like to come in
and join us for some tea?

210
00:11:01,750 --> 00:11:04,041
Yup! If that's okay with Nina.

211
00:11:04,125 --> 00:11:06,125
Sure.

212
00:11:06,208 --> 00:11:08,291
What's that number one
badge for?

213
00:11:08,375 --> 00:11:10,000
--[YUKO] Oh, this?
--[AOI] There she is!

214
00:11:10,083 --> 00:11:12,458
Hey, Lion.

215
00:11:12,541 --> 00:11:15,625
Do you mind wearing this badge
on your jacket for the day?

216
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:18,416
Goodness, looks like
you've been nominated

217
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,583
for the Miss Pirari Contest too.

218
00:11:20,666 --> 00:11:22,166
So that's what these are for.

219
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:23,375
[BELLE whines]

220
00:11:23,458 --> 00:11:25,750
[STRAFANSKY]
Behold! The angel of my country!

221
00:11:25,833 --> 00:11:26,583
Isn't she cute?

222
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:28,458
Look at that adorable face!

223
00:11:28,541 --> 00:11:29,791
Lion!

224
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:32,125
Please cast your vote
for my wonderful daughter.

225
00:11:32,208 --> 00:11:34,416
Badge number six!

226
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:36,291
[MIZUKI] Pirari Academy's
number one beauty

227
00:11:36,375 --> 00:11:37,458
will steal your heart!

228
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:39,791
Her name's Yuko Morigaya!

229
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:42,125
So hurry up and vote
for badge number one.

230
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:45,375
But remember that
Yuko belongs to me alone!

231
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,333
[STRAFANSKY yells]

232
00:11:49,416 --> 00:11:51,083
[MIZUKI yells]

233
00:11:51,166 --> 00:11:53,500
[BOTH yelling]

234
00:11:53,583 --> 00:11:55,000
[BOTH groan]

235
00:11:57,083 --> 00:11:58,708
[LINYA]
Hello, Honey.

236
00:11:58,791 --> 00:11:59,750
[STRAFANSKY gasps]

237
00:12:01,458 --> 00:12:02,791
What a surprise!

238
00:12:02,875 --> 00:12:05,583
[LINYA] And don't worry,
the kitty cat is safe and sound.

239
00:12:05,666 --> 00:12:08,291
[STRAFANSKY]
Wait! Let me explain!

240
00:12:10,041 --> 00:12:11,500
[PRINCIPAL humming]

241
00:12:11,583 --> 00:12:13,625
What are your thoughts on our
first ever school festival?

242
00:12:13,708 --> 00:12:16,083
It looks like everyone
is enjoying themselves.

243
00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:17,875
That's good. I was
a bit nervous since we've

244
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:19,708
never entertained
this many people before.

245
00:12:19,791 --> 00:12:23,500
[CROWD chattering]

246
00:12:23,583 --> 00:12:25,916
Look! Father and Mother
are both here.

247
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,916
I didn't expect
both of them to show up.

248
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:30,333
I see Mistress's mother
is in the audience too.

249
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:33,000
I guess her father must've
been too busy with work.

250
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:35,250
Come on, ladies!
We're having a pre-show meeting!

251
00:12:35,333 --> 00:12:36,375
Understood.

252
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:40,000
[MAHIRO]
This is the real deal.

253
00:12:40,083 --> 00:12:43,083
Thank you all for working
so hard on this project with me.

254
00:12:43,166 --> 00:12:44,666
I hope that everyone
watching our play

255
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:46,208
will be more interested
in Foreigners

256
00:12:46,291 --> 00:12:48,666
after hearing a song
from another world.

257
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:49,750
Here we go.

258
00:12:49,833 --> 00:12:51,708
Let's give it our all out there!

259
00:12:51,791 --> 00:12:53,500
[ALL]
Yeah!

260
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:58,541
[CROWD murmuring]

261
00:12:58,625 --> 00:13:01,500
[buzzing]

262
00:13:06,708 --> 00:13:09,583
Even though our village has
lost its only water source,

263
00:13:09,666 --> 00:13:12,208
we can't let you go out
into the dangerous forest.

264
00:13:12,291 --> 00:13:15,625
You'd only end up
being eaten by the witch!

265
00:13:15,708 --> 00:13:18,791
Maybe. But if someone doesn't
go out and find water soon,

266
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:20,875
we'll surely all die of thirst.

267
00:13:20,958 --> 00:13:22,333
[FEMALE STUDENT 9A] The well
dried up without warning

268
00:13:22,416 --> 00:13:23,916
several days ago.

269
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:28,250
As far as we know, this might be
the work of that evil witch too.

270
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:30,583
[MAHIRO hooting]

271
00:13:30,666 --> 00:13:31,750
This can't be.

272
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,125
If the forest brook's not here

273
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:35,500
then that means it
must've dried up too.

274
00:13:35,583 --> 00:13:37,708
How will I get any water?

275
00:13:40,583 --> 00:13:44,583
[LION] ♪ Many years
and months have passed ♪

276
00:13:44,666 --> 00:13:48,666
♪ Since last I laid eyes
on my world ♪

277
00:13:48,750 --> 00:13:52,541
♪ Yet I have a wish that lasts ♪

278
00:13:52,625 --> 00:13:56,208
♪ Even with time
my hope never faded ♪

279
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:58,250
Please tell me who you are.

280
00:13:58,333 --> 00:14:01,375
The people of your world
often call me a witch.

281
00:14:01,458 --> 00:14:03,500
[NINA] What is that song
you were singing?

282
00:14:03,583 --> 00:14:04,708
You heard?

283
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:07,125
[NINA]
Yes. It was beautiful.

284
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:10,083
Does that mean you're
really not afraid of me?

285
00:14:13,125 --> 00:14:15,625
I can't let you collapse
out here in the forest.

286
00:14:15,708 --> 00:14:19,416
The wild animals would love
nothing more than to eat you.

287
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:23,875
By showing me this spring,
you've saved my entire village.

288
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:25,291
Thank you so much.

289
00:14:25,375 --> 00:14:27,083
You don't need to thank me.

290
00:14:27,166 --> 00:14:30,500
This water's been one with the
earth long before I arrived.

291
00:14:30,583 --> 00:14:32,458
It doesn't belong to me.

292
00:14:32,541 --> 00:14:34,875
I refuse to believe
that you're really a witch.

293
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:38,000
An evil person wouldn't
have helped me like this.

294
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:39,583
What can I say.

295
00:14:39,666 --> 00:14:42,083
That is what the people
of this world call me.

296
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:44,416
And I've never chosen
a different name.

297
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:46,541
You're such a mysterious girl.

298
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:48,583
Where did you come from?

299
00:14:48,666 --> 00:14:52,083
Unlike you, this strange planet
we're on is not my home.

300
00:14:52,166 --> 00:14:54,166
I came from another world.

301
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,416
[NINA]
How is that possible?

302
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:58,583
[FEMALE STUDENT 9C]
Look everybody, she came back!

303
00:14:58,666 --> 00:15:01,666
Keep it up!
Your acting is spot on!

304
00:15:01,750 --> 00:15:03,750
Leave everything
to me, director.

305
00:15:03,833 --> 00:15:06,875
Just keep doing what you're
doing for the rest of the play!

306
00:15:06,958 --> 00:15:08,916
[FEMALE STUDENT 9A]
It's water! Clean water!

307
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,250
[FEMALE STUDENT 9C]
She brought back water

308
00:15:10,333 --> 00:15:12,416
from a running spring
found deep in the forest.

309
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:14,833
The village will
live on after all!

310
00:15:14,916 --> 00:15:15,958
Here.

311
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,666
Thanks, Yayoi.

312
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:19,958
[YAYOI] I can tell you're
pretty nervous on stage.

313
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:21,250
Yeah.

314
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:23,583
A little but I'll be okay.

315
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:25,625
That's a good thing.

316
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:27,625
Nervousness comes from
the feelings one gets

317
00:15:27,708 --> 00:15:29,125
when they really
want to succeed.

318
00:15:29,208 --> 00:15:31,291
Or at least that's what
my great-great-grandfather

319
00:15:31,375 --> 00:15:32,375
used to say.

320
00:15:32,458 --> 00:15:33,875
Seeing you nervous
proves that you're

321
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:36,583
giving your very best today.

322
00:15:36,666 --> 00:15:38,250
That means a lot.

323
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:42,125
This spring belongs to us now!

324
00:15:42,208 --> 00:15:43,958
We won't let that
evil witch have it!

325
00:15:44,041 --> 00:15:45,583
[STUDENTS]
We'll defend our water!

326
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:47,875
This awful drought has caused
every tree in the forest

327
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,750
to shrivel up and die.

328
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:52,375
This is bad!

329
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:54,125
This fire's getting
out of control!

330
00:15:54,208 --> 00:15:56,291
At this rate,
the village will catch fire!

331
00:15:56,375 --> 00:15:58,083
[FEMALE STUDENT 9A]
How can we stop it?

332
00:16:02,916 --> 00:16:04,208
It can't be.

333
00:16:04,291 --> 00:16:05,791
The village is burning.

334
00:16:05,875 --> 00:16:08,833
[LION] There is a certain legend
told by the people of my world.

335
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:10,833
Can you tell it to me?

336
00:16:10,916 --> 00:16:12,791
If two people
from separate worlds

337
00:16:12,875 --> 00:16:15,250
come together peacefully
and join their hearts as one,

338
00:16:15,333 --> 00:16:17,875
they can gain new powers and--

339
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:19,416
[gasps]

340
00:16:26,625 --> 00:16:27,750
[groans]

341
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:29,958
[gasps]

342
00:16:31,416 --> 00:16:32,458
[CROWD murmurs]

343
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:34,000
--Poor Lion!
--[CROWD murmurs]

344
00:16:34,083 --> 00:16:37,416
[CROWD murmurs]

345
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,708
I-I don't know what I should do.

346
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:41,583
Oh no, Lion's lost her Trance.

347
00:16:41,666 --> 00:16:43,458
What a disaster.

348
00:16:44,125 --> 00:16:46,500
[LION whimpers]

349
00:16:48,416 --> 00:16:50,125
Follow my lead.

350
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:56,625
Sing your song.

351
00:16:56,708 --> 00:16:58,541
Let's save the village...

352
00:16:58,625 --> 00:16:59,916
...together.

353
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,458
[LION]
Mm. I'd like that very much.

354
00:17:02,541 --> 00:17:03,875
Together.

355
00:17:05,458 --> 00:17:09,458
[LION, NINA] ♪ Many years
and months have passed ♪

356
00:17:09,541 --> 00:17:13,458
♪ Since last I laid eyes
on my world ♪

357
00:17:13,541 --> 00:17:17,583
♪ Yet I have a wish that lasts ♪

358
00:17:17,666 --> 00:17:21,250
♪ Even with time
my hope's never faded ♪

359
00:17:21,333 --> 00:17:25,583
♪ If you'll take my hand,
you'll hear it too ♪

360
00:17:25,666 --> 00:17:31,250
♪ A soft and gentle voice ♪

361
00:17:31,333 --> 00:17:35,416
♪ As long as I
stay close to you ♪

362
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:39,541
♪ Then both our hearts
will beat as one. ♪

363
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:43,666
♪ Show me a smile
There's no need for prayers ♪

364
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:47,541
♪ Your heart lets me know
that you care ♪

365
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:51,625
♪ A soul inside
that does beguile ♪

366
00:17:51,708 --> 00:17:54,583
♪ Shines as bright as the sun ♪

367
00:17:54,666 --> 00:17:59,791
♪ It calls out to me
It echoes inside ♪

368
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:06,041
♪ Keeping beat with my heart
just like a song ♪

369
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:07,666
[rain falls]

370
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:10,458
It's rain! The first rain
we've had in months!

371
00:18:10,541 --> 00:18:12,333
And it's putting the fire out!

372
00:18:12,416 --> 00:18:15,333
Do you think that pretty song
is responsible for this?

373
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:18,833
Which two girls could've
sung such a miraculous song?

374
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:21,166
One voice was from our village.

375
00:18:21,250 --> 00:18:22,958
But what about the other singer?

376
00:18:23,041 --> 00:18:24,125
Wow.

377
00:18:24,208 --> 00:18:26,125
Maybe it's a goddess!

378
00:18:27,666 --> 00:18:29,125
[STUDENTS]
It's the witch!

379
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:32,708
But this is the
so-called goddess

380
00:18:32,791 --> 00:18:34,625
you were just talking about.

381
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:37,500
See, she's not an evil witch.

382
00:18:37,583 --> 00:18:40,000
She's a friend
from a different world.

383
00:18:40,083 --> 00:18:42,333
All she wants is
to live with us.

384
00:18:47,333 --> 00:18:48,875
[applause]

385
00:18:48,958 --> 00:18:53,458
--[CROWD cheers]
--[applause]

386
00:18:53,541 --> 00:18:57,041
[STRAFANSKY sobs]
Bravo! Bravo!

387
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:58,208
[RINO giggles]

388
00:18:58,291 --> 00:19:01,041
--[CROWD cheering]
--[STRAFANSKY crying]

389
00:19:01,125 --> 00:19:05,416
--[CROWD cheering]
--[STRAFANSKY] She's amazing!

390
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:06,583
--[CROWD cheering]
--That's my daughter!

391
00:19:06,666 --> 00:19:10,208
--[CROWD cheering]
--I love you!

392
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:14,625
[LION]
Mommy!

393
00:19:14,708 --> 00:19:16,541
I'm so happy you came!

394
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:18,333
Lion! My sweet baby girl!

395
00:19:18,416 --> 00:19:19,666
Nothing could've stopped me.

396
00:19:19,750 --> 00:19:20,500
[LION giggles]

397
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:22,958
B-But Daddy came too.

398
00:19:23,041 --> 00:19:24,583
Everyone was wonderful.

399
00:19:24,666 --> 00:19:26,208
You get big gold stars.

400
00:19:26,291 --> 00:19:27,208
[KAGURA]
Mm-hm.

401
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:28,583
[MAHIRO laughs]

402
00:19:28,666 --> 00:19:29,916
--[YAYOI] What did I tell you...
--[MAHIRO] Good job.

403
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:30,916
[VERONICA]
Excuse me girls.

404
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:31,958
[NINA gasps]

405
00:19:34,166 --> 00:19:36,083
Oh, hello, Bureau Chief.

406
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:39,083
I see that you're
fitting in at the academy.

407
00:19:39,166 --> 00:19:41,291
Well, I'm trying to.

408
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:43,458
Please excuse me Chief,

409
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:46,000
but there're some people
who'd like to meet you.

410
00:19:46,083 --> 00:19:47,041
[VERONICA]
Nina.

411
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,208
Enjoy your school life.

412
00:19:51,666 --> 00:19:54,375
Were you just talking to
Bureau Chief Veronica?

413
00:19:54,458 --> 00:19:55,708
She's amazing!

414
00:19:55,791 --> 00:19:57,875
I've never seen her
in person before.

415
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:05,916
Hey, the big award ceremony's
just about to start!

416
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:08,666
Nina, you look upset.
Is there something wrong?

417
00:20:10,041 --> 00:20:11,208
No, it's nothing.

418
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:12,583
We better go.

419
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:16,833
[STUDENTS chattering]

420
00:20:16,916 --> 00:20:18,416
[MIZUKI]
The votes have been counted,

421
00:20:18,500 --> 00:20:22,375
and now it's time to crown our
fist ever Miss Pirari Academy.

422
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:28,958
[gasps] And the winner is...

423
00:20:29,041 --> 00:20:33,041
...entry number one,
Yuko Morigaya!

424
00:20:33,125 --> 00:20:34,375
--[STUDENTS cheering]
--Huh?

425
00:20:34,458 --> 00:20:35,583
--[STUDENTS cheering]
--The election was rigged!

426
00:20:35,666 --> 00:20:37,000
I really won?

427
00:20:37,083 --> 00:20:39,666
You're so charming that
nobody else ever stood a chance!

428
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:41,416
Congratulations.

429
00:20:44,166 --> 00:20:47,166
[AOI] We'll now announce the
winner of the stage division.

430
00:20:49,625 --> 00:20:53,583
[STUDENTS chattering]

431
00:20:53,666 --> 00:20:55,208
[YAYOI]
It took a lot of hugging,

432
00:20:55,291 --> 00:20:58,208
but Lion's father
finally stopped crying.

433
00:20:58,291 --> 00:21:00,333
And it didn't take long
for Lion to cheer up too,

434
00:21:00,416 --> 00:21:02,333
once he quit making a scene.

435
00:21:05,958 --> 00:21:08,458
[YAYOI] It's too bad that
we only got second place.

436
00:21:08,541 --> 00:21:10,375
But I think everybody
understood the message

437
00:21:10,458 --> 00:21:13,833
you were trying to get across
with that Foreigner song.

438
00:21:13,916 --> 00:21:16,541
And of course,
the same goes for me.

439
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:19,750
[YAYOI]
Hm?

440
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:24,833
[MAHIRO snoring]

441
00:21:30,208 --> 00:21:32,833
[YAYOI] Thanks for all
your hard work, Mahiro.

442
00:23:06,458 --> 00:23:08,791
[STRAFANSKY]
This is my wife. Ha, ha, ha!

443
00:23:08,875 --> 00:23:11,750
[RINO] So now we have Lion's
mother to deal with too.

444
00:23:11,833 --> 00:23:13,458
I'm sorry about my husband.

445
00:23:13,541 --> 00:23:15,458
He's caused you all
so much trouble.

446
00:23:15,541 --> 00:23:17,416
[KAGURA]
Nothing less from a First Lady.

447
00:23:17,500 --> 00:23:19,291
[KOZUE] The other teachers
and I have often wondered

448
00:23:19,375 --> 00:23:21,750
what made you fall in love
with Lion's father.

449
00:23:21,833 --> 00:23:23,500
Good question. I'm curious.

450
00:23:23,583 --> 00:23:25,166
[KOZUE]
Is it what I'm thinking?

451
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:26,666
You know what I'm
getting at, right?

452
00:23:26,750 --> 00:23:27,916
[RINO]
You're being so vague

453
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,541
that I have no idea
what you're hinting at.

454
00:23:29,625 --> 00:23:30,916
[LINYA]
Let me think.

455
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:33,291
Well, it was a
combination of things.

456
00:23:34,125 --> 00:23:36,458
But I think what really
sealed the deal for me

457
00:23:36,541 --> 00:23:39,083
was his promise to always
spend birthdays together.

458
00:23:39,166 --> 00:23:40,333
He would bring me roses,

459
00:23:40,416 --> 00:23:42,916
no matter what battlefield
I was fighting on.

460
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,416
[KOZUE] That would definitely
set my heart aflutter.

461
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,583
It worked for me!

462
00:23:46,666 --> 00:23:47,791
[RINO]
That's sweet,

463
00:23:47,875 --> 00:23:49,750
but I'm gonna need
all the juicy details!

464
00:23:49,833 --> 00:23:50,916
[LINYA, STRAFANSKY]
Uh--

